This phase evolves the workstation's parsing engine into a high-fidelity forensic orchestrator. "Ultimate Mode" will now force execution of all available parsers, bypass category filtering, and generate timestamped serialized JSON dumps for historical tracking. We also introduce a tri-profile VLC system and a Forensic Integrity Auditor to flag metadata discrepancies.

User Review Required
IMPORTANT

Storage & History: "Ultimate Mode" will generate additional files in data/forensic_exports/. As requested, these will be timestamped (e.g., filename.20231027_120000.forensic.json) to allow for historical analysis of how metadata changes over time or across different versions.

Forensic Validation: We are introducing a validation layer that compares results between parsers (e.g., VLC vs FFprobe). Any discrepancies in critical fields (duration, codec, bitrate) will be flagged in a new validation_flags field.

